    <title>Water contributor: Max Gomberg</title>
    <description>Max Gomberg is the water conservation and climate change manager at the State Water Resources Control Board, where he has led development of emergency water conservation regulations among other initiatives. Previously, he was a senior analyst for the Office of Ratepayer Advocates at the California Public Utilities Commission. He holds a Masters degree in Public Policy from UCLA and a BA in Environmental Studies from the University of Chicago.
</description>
